**basic commands (pwd, cd, mkdir, ls, cp, mv, rm)

pwd
    print working directory, shows current location

cd 
    change directory

mkdir 
    make directory
    use -p and slashes between to create parent/nested directories

        mkdir -p genetics/lab 
            this will create one working directory "genetics" with a directory "lab" within it

ls 
    list files and directories
        -f shows types
        -l long format
        -a hidden files 
        -h human readable sizes
        -lrth shows file size

    
        blue- directory- you can cd to it
        white/grey- regular file - you can cat,less,head,tail it
        red- compressed file - must unzip first
        green- executable file

wc
    to list the number of files or lines
    
        wc -l shows the number of files within directory or folder

        ls code | wc -l
            lists the number of folders within code

cp 
    copy  command+source+destination

    cp -r 
        copies directories
    
    if you want to move a file to a directory
        cp filename directory/

    if you want to move a folder to a directory
        cp -p folder directory/

    if you want to copy a file to current directory under a new name
        cp oldfoldername newfoldername 

    move a file to new directory and name at same time
        cp olderfoldername directory/newfoldername 
    
mv 
    move and rename , removes old file destination
    make sure the current directory is destination

    just rename folders
         mv oldfoldername/ newfoldername/

    move two at once
         mv oldfile.txt oldfile2.txt folder/


    
rm
