    LOOPS

    $ for 
    >do
    >
    >mv
    >done 

    for example
    
    $ for filename in *.txt
    >do> name=$(basename ${filename} .txt)
    >mv ${filename} ${name}_2019.txt
    > done

$ for starts the loop, 
    $ for filename in *.txt 
        looks for every file in this folder that ends in .txt and puts 
        in a temperary bucket called filename 

>do>  action

name=$ (down below)
    creates a variable

(basename ${filename} .txt)

    whats in the perentheses before

    strips the extension, takes the current file (ex. sample_1.txt) and 
    removes the .txt (sample_1)

>mv ${filename} ${name}_2019.txt

    renames -new name + _2019.txt
    for example sample_1_2019.txt

>done finalizes changes and closes loop

